title: UGA overcomes Beck's 3 INTs, rallies past Florida
description: Despite three interceptions from Carson Beck, Georgia earned its fourth straight win over Florida with a 34-20 victory Saturday.

title: Source: RB Elliott out due to disciplinary reasons
description: Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott will not play Sunday against the Atlanta Falcons because of disciplinary reasons, a source told ESPN on Saturday.
author: Todd Archer

title: Livingstone's ton powers England past West Indies
description: A spectacular maiden ODI century from stand-in captain Liam Livingstone helps England defeat West Indies by five wickets.

title: Ford focus can't obscure England's other shortcomings
description: George Ford's missed kicks and missed tackles obscured other failings that England must address to rescue their autumn campaign.

title: Pep, Walker highlight lack of recovery after shock defeat
description: Pep Guardiola suggested the fact Man City had less time recovery time played a part in their shock defeat to Bournemouth at the Vitality Stadium.

title: Sao Paulo GP race time changed in unprecedented move after Qualy postponed
description: The Sao Paulo Grand Prix start has been moved 90 minutes earlier - with Qualifying also taking place on Sunday morning - as bad weather wreaked havoc with the event's schedule.

title: Penn State didn't recruit Ohio State's Will Howard. He got his revenge
description: Howard dreamed of playing for Penn State as a kid, but never got a chance. He didn't play his best in Happy Valley, but he did just enough to win.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: No. 11 Iowa State suffers first loss of season, falling 23-22 to Texas Tech in final seconds
description: The Cyclones took the lead with just over two minutes remaining, but that gave the Red Raiders enough time to drive for the go-ahead score.
author: Yahoo Sports
